{{Quote|Perhaps if you grow ''talkative'' enough, ''soon'' enough... there'll be a chance to ''save'' him... before the War Sled finishes rocketing down this ''particular'' branch of the canyon... which ''ends'' at the great ''Geyser Sea''!|Imperial Commander|<ref name="death trap" />}}
The '''Geyser Sea''' was a body of [[Water/Legends|water]] located on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Akuria II]]. The sea was kept warm through a system of hot [[Geyser/Legends|geysers]] beneath it that also seemed to have the effect of changing the [[Color/Legends|color]] of the water to an orange hue. The [[Akuria Rebel Base]] was internally heated by diverting a portion of the Geyser Sea into the base.<ref name="treachery">{{StoryCite|story=Treachery!|book=Pizzazz 12}}</ref>

After [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] and [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] discovered his true identity, the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Commander/Legends|commander]] who had been [[Odan (impostor)|impersonating]] the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] leader [[Odan]] trapped Luke inside a runaway [[War Sled]] that was careening toward the Geyser Sea.<ref name="death trap" /> Luke was rescued by Odan, [[Fafnir]], [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]], and [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] at the last moment.<ref name="snow fury">{{StoryCite|story=Snow Fury!|book=Pizzazz 14}}</ref>

